The '''2003 Thailand Open''' was a men's [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Tennis court#Indoor courts|indoor hard courts]]. It was the inaugural edition of the [[PTT Thailand Open (ATP)|Thailand Open]], and was part of the [[ATP International Series|International Series]] of the [[2003 ATP Tour]]. It took place at the [[Impact, Muang Thong Thani|Impact Arena]] in [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]], from 22 September through 29 September 2003. Eight-seeded [[Taylor Dent]] won the singles title.

==Champions==

===Singles===
{{main|2003 Thailand Open – Singles}}
{{flagicon|USA}} '''[[Taylor Dent]]''' defeated {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Juan Carlos Ferrero]], 6–3, 7–6<sup>(7–5)</sup><ref name="Singles">{{Cite web|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/Share/Event-Draws.aspx?e=1720&y=2003|title=2003 Thailand Open Singles Draw|accessdate=2010-10-04|publisher=[[Association of Tennis Professionals]]}}</ref>
*It was Dent's 2nd title of the year, and his 3rd overall.

===Doubles===
{{main|2003 Thailand Open – Doubles}}
{{flagicon|ISR}} '''[[Jonathan Erlich]]''' / {{flagicon|ISR}} '''[[Andy Ram]]''' defeated {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Andrew Kratzmann]] / {{flagicon|FIN}} [[Jarkko Nieminen]], 6–3, 7–6<sup>(7–4)</sup><ref name="Doubles">{{Cite web|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/Share/Event-Draws.aspx?e=1720&y=2003&t=d|title=2003 Thailand Open Doubles Draw|accessdate=2010-10-04|publisher=[[Association of Tennis Professionals]]}}</ref>
*It was Jonathan Erlich's 1st title of the year, also 2nd overall. It was Andy Ram's 2nd title of the year and his 2nd overall. This marked the team's 1st title.

