The '''Barbados Football Association''' is the governing body of [[association football]] in [[Barbados]]. It is responsible the administration of football in Barbados with responsibility for the [[Barbados national football team|Barbadian national football team]] as well as the other Barbados National Football teams. Established in 1910, it was originally named the Barbados Football Amateur Association, but changed in 1925 to the current name. The Barbados Football Association became affiliated to [[FIFA]] in 1968, [[CONCACAF]] in 1967 and also the [[Caribbean Football Union]].

