{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
'''Estadio José Picasso Peratta''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Ica (city)|Ica]], [[Peru]].  It is currently used by [[football (soccer)]] teams [[Octavio Espinoza de Ica|Octavio Espinoza]] and [[Estudiantes de Medicina]]. The stadium holds 8,000 people, but the owners are planning to expand it to 15,000.
Its name comes from a former mayor of Ica, José Picasso Perata, which together with the Picasso family helped to build and finance the stadium.

{{coord|14.0680|S|75.7390|W|source:wikidata|display=title}}

