{{Infobox football biography |name = Francisco Atura |image = |caption = |fullname = Francisco Alam Atura |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1979|8|1|df=y}} |birth_place = |height = |position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] |years1 = 1998–2001 |clubs1 = [[Santiago Wanderers]] |caps1 = |goals1 = |years2 = 2001–2004 |clubs2 = [[Unión La Calera]] |caps2 = |goals2 = |years3 = 2005–2006 |clubs3 = [[Unión San Felipe]] |caps3 = |goals3 = |totalcaps = |totalgoals = |nationalyears1 = 2002–2006 |nationalteam1 = [[Palestine national football team|Palestine]] |nationalcaps1 = 24 |nationalgoals1 = 3 }} '''Francisco Alam Atura''' (born 1 August 1979) is a [[State of Palestine|Palestinian]] former professional [[association football|footballer]] who played at both professional and international levels as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]].
==Career== Atura spent his entire professional career in Chile, playing with [[Santiago Wanderers]], [[Unión La Calera]] and [[Unión San Felipe]].<ref name = "NFT">{{NFT player|pid=5037}}</ref>
Atura earned 24 caps for the [[Palestine national football team|Palestinian national side]] between 2002 and 2006,<ref name = "NFT"/> appearing in five FIFA World Cup qualifying matches.<ref>{{FIFA player|210238}}</ref>
