{{Infobox Stadium | |name = ''Stadion 17 Mei'' |image = [[File:17 May Stadium.jpg|300px]] |location = [[Banjarmasin]], Indonesia |fullname = May 17 Stadium |coordinates = |broke_ground = |opened = 17 May 1974 |closed = |demolished = |owner = [[National Sports Committee of Indonesia|South Kalimantan KONI]]| |operator = |surface = Grass |construction_cost = |architect = |former_name = |tenants = [[PS Barito Putera|Barito Putera]] |seating_capacity = 15,000 }} '''May 17th Stadium''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] located in [[Banjarmasin]], Indonesia. It is currently used mostly for [[association football|football]] matches. The stadium holds 15,000 people. It is the home stadium of [[PS Barito Putera|Barito Putera]], which was considered as one of the major football clubs in Indonesia in [[1994–95 Liga Indonesia Premier Division|1994/95 Premier Division]].
==History== The Stadium originally opened to the public in May 17, 1974 as a [[Multi-purpose stadium]] with a capacity around 5.000. it's undergone renovations three times first in 1988 with the last major one in 2008 and a third one for 2012.
