{{Redirect|MVP|the documentary film|Most Valuable Players (film)|other uses|MVP (disambiguation)}}
{{refimprove|date=August 2018}}
[[File:FrankNighbor.jpg|right|thumb|[[Frank Nighbor]] with the original [[Hart Memorial Trophy]] in 1924.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hhof.com/htmlSilverware/silver_splashhart.shtml|website=Official website of Hockey Hall of Fame|title=Hart Memorial Trophy|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref> The trophy is awarded annually to the "player judged most valuable to his team" in the [[National Hockey League]] (NHL).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nhl.com/ice/page.htm?id=24934|website=NHL.com|title=Hart Memorial Trophy|accessdate=15 February 2018|quote=The Hart Memorial Trophy is an annual award given to the player judged to be the most valuable to his team.}}</ref>]]
In [[sport|sports]], a '''most valuable player''' ('''MVP''') [[award]] is an honor typically bestowed upon the best-performing player (or players) in an entire league, for a particular competition, or on a specific team. Initially used in professional sports, the term is now also commonly used in amateur sports, as well as in other completely unrelated fields such as business and music. In many sports, MVP awards are presented for a specific match—in other words, a [[man of the match]] award.
The term is most common in the [[United States]] and [[Canada]]. In other cases, "[[player of the year award|player of the year]]" is used. In Australia, [[Australian rules football]] clubs and leagues use the term "[[best and fairest]]", while those playing [[rugby league]] use "player of the year", such as the [[Dally M Medal]].<ref>[http://www.nrl.com/thurston-wins-2015-dally-m-medal/tabid/10874/newsid/90203/default.aspx Dally M Medal 2015]</ref> The [[National Basketball League (Australia)|National Basketball League]], however, uses the American-style "MVP" for its awards.
In many cases the awards are voted on by members of the [[sports journalism|media]]. In others the vote is by players, [[coach (sports)|coaches]], or umpires. In recent years, [[online voting|online polls]] from the public decide some awards.
==Sports== Examples include: * [[Major League Baseball]]'s [[Major League Baseball Most Valuable Player Award|American and National Leagues]], [[League Championship Series Most Valuable Player Award|AL & NL Championship Series]], and [[World Series Most Valuable Player Award|World Series]]; also [[Major League Baseball All-Star Game Most Valuable Player Award|All-Star Game]] * [[National Football League Most Valuable Player Award|National Football League regular season]] and [[Super Bowl Most Valuable Player Award|Super Bowl]]; also [[Pro Bowl MVP|Pro Bowl]] * [[Hart Memorial Trophy]] and [[Ted Lindsay Award|Lester B. Pearson/Ted Lindsay Award]] ([[National Hockey League]] regular season) and [[Conn Smythe Trophy]] ([[Stanley Cup playoffs|playoffs]]); the [[National Hockey League All-Star Game|All-Star Game]] also has an MVP * [[NBA Most Valuable Player Award|National Basketball Association regular season]] and [[Bill Russell NBA Finals Most Valuable Player Award|Finals]]; also [[NBA_All-Star_Game_Most_Valuable_Player_Award|NBA All-Star Game]] * [[EuroLeague MVP]] * [[Landon Donovan MVP Award|Major League Soccer regular season]] and [[MLS Cup#Most Valuable Player Award|MLS Cup]]; also [[Major League Soccer All-Star Game|MLS All-Star Game]] * [[FIVB]] Tournaments * [[CFL's Most Outstanding Player Award|Canadian Football League regular season]], [[Terry Evanshen Trophy|East Division]], [[Jeff Nicklin Memorial Trophy|West Division]], and [[Grey Cup Most Valuable Player|Grey Cup]]; also "Most Valuable Canadian" awards for the [[CFL's Most Outstanding Canadian Award|regular season]] and [[Dick Suderman Trophy|Grey Cup]] * [[College football]]'s [[Heisman Trophy]] * [[NCAA Basketball Tournament Most Outstanding Player|NCAA Basketball Tournament]]; there are also various awards for [[List of U.S. men's college basketball national player of the year awards|the player(s) selected as player of the year]] * [[Indian Premier League]]<ref>[http://www.cricinfo.com/magazine/content/story/352877.html Most valuable player in IPL]</ref> * [[NBL Most Valuable Player Award|National Basketball League regular season]] and [[NBL Grand Final Most Valuable Player Award|Grand Final]] * [[Leigh Matthews Trophy]], given by the [[AFL Players Association]] to the [[Australian Football League|AFL]]'s ''most valuable player'' (as opposed to the [[Brownlow Medal]], given to the ''[[best and fairest|fairest and best]]'') * [[Philippine Basketball Association Most Valuable Player award|Philippine Basketball Association regular season]]
==See also== * [[Best and fairest]] * [[Athlete of the Year]] * [[Man of the match]] * [[Player of the year award]] * [[Most Outstanding Player (disambiguation)]]
